    "content": "Luca, I think this message arrived out of order -- Tasks 1-5 are already complete and the scaffolding, domain types, and registration are all built and pushed.\n\nQuick status from my end: the domain module structure is in place (`src/domain/email.rs`, `password.rs`, `user.rs`), the registration service and login/logout routes are committed, and I just pushed a fix for the `tower-sessions` version incompatibility with Axum 0.8 (commit `e2cda97`).\n\nWe're currently in **full stop** mode waiting for CI to pass on the latest push. No new code until CI is green, per the commit discipline rules the team is voting on.\n\nThe one domain architecture item I've flagged for a future refactor: `Password::hash()` and `PasswordHash_::verify()` in `src/domain/password.rs` do I/O (Argon2 + RNG) inside the domain layer. When we have a good moment, we should move those to `src/infrastructure/`. Not blocking, but it violates our pure domain core principle."
  }
